<br>
Do all mages experience times like this?  Where you need to take a week off the experience treadmill to raise money for gems, farm cash for spells, go find a fire drake scale, and little things like that?  My druid used to do errands like this in his sleep, but with my mage it's all so time-consuming.  I actually enjoy it somewhat-- it makes the rewards mean more when you have to work for them.  It's just that I'm always hearing about people blasting through levels with very little /played time.  I'm wondering if the delays I'm experiencing are common for mages from time to time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulionfrog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lionfrog</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 216<br> <font color=#333333>(8/10/02 1:51:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=167.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Level 24 Research/Focus Hell</span><hr size=1> That has been my WHOLE EQ life except mine was WAY worse than your experience (I'm going on 3 years with this one char and hes only 26). <br>
<br>
I spent about 1 month getting ALL of my focus items, First I found a nice MAGE in OOT named &quot;KYLERE&quot; (Where has he gone? He used to be on this board a lot!) Who got me ALL of my giants toes from my friend &quot;Gornit&quot;. <br>
<br>
Then I tried Najena (before the change) to get all the brooms and shovels and steins and torches, no chance! I bought ALL of the Gems and got all of the creature components but I still hadn't gotten my Torch, Broom, Shovel, and Stein. <br>
<br>
So, I went to the dastardly place called &quot;Cazic Thule&quot; This was WAY WAY before the  change was made on that zone. The  most BEAUTIFUL High Elf Yadilu helped me get all those stupid gardening tools by killing  the gators for about 4 hours with me, I was level 21 so I couldn't really help much, but she was 49 and gators were fairly easy for her. She was SOOOO SOOOOOOOOOO GREAT, I wish everyone on EQ was like her *sigh*. <br>
<br>
So THEN a month after I started with the toes I got the items and hadn't gained a level. <br>
<br>
*           *           *<br>
<br>
<br>
Something I learned about getting ready for the 24 jump and research was to fight in LOIO *YUCK* and check all the vendors in Firona Vie for components.  Also, DON'T use ANY of your skill points for  ANYTHING but spell research, it will help GREATLY if you use all your skill point to up your level in Spell Research. <br>
<br>
If you know any nice magi who are of a higher level (I used Yadilu) ask him/her to research the items for you, make sure you have a few extra components for the spells because they might mess up once at most if they have practiced research.<br>
<br>
You are not alone!!!!<br>
<br>
